parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature failure of the rear wheel bearing can lead to catastrophic failure while traveling at high speeds, resulting in loss of control, accidents, and potential injury or death to the operator.
symptoms: Accelerated wear on the rear wheel bearings
pitted and gritty feeling on the bearing
bearing failure at low mileage (around 9
000 miles).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator stator can cause the battery to drain, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The battery is not charging
the engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the battery drains quickly
the vehicle stalls on the highway
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the plastic fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and serious injuries or fatalities, especially since the tank is positioned directly over the exhaust system.
symptoms: Fuel smell during or after riding
visible cracks on the fuel tank
fuel leaks
hissing sounds from the fuel tank area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine while riding can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine dies or stalls while riding
especially when rolling off the throttle to slow down
the tachometer shows incorrect readings (e.g.
000 RPM when the engine is dead)
the engine dies again after restarting
the longer the bike is turned off
the longer it will run before dying again
no warning or check engine lights appear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable throttle response can cause sudden acceleration or deceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-miss incidents, especially during low-speed maneuvering or when driving over road deformities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected acceleration or deceleration
rapid throttle response without warning
loss of traction or control
especially at low speeds
and difficulty maintaining a steady speed or trajectory.
